paw /pɔː/

(pawing,pawed,paws) 

1. N-COUNT The paws of an animal such as a cat, dog, or bear are its feet, which have claws for gripping things and soft pads for walking on. 脚爪 

例： The kitten was black with white front paws and a white splotch on her chest. 那只小猫除了白色前爪和胸部的一块白色区域外是黑色的。 

2. V-T/V-I If an animal paws something, or paws at it, it draws its foot over it or down it. 用脚抓; 用脚刨 

例： Madigan's horse pawed the ground. 马迪根的马刨了地。 

3. V-T/V-I If one person paws another, or paws at them, they touch or stroke them in a way that the other person finds offensive. (冒犯性地) 抚摸 [表不满] 

例： Stop pawing me, Geraldo! 杰拉尔多，别摸我！

